Module io.inverno.mod.http.base
Package io.inverno.mod.http.base.router

Interface QueryParametersRoute<A>

All Superinterfaces:
Route<A>
public interface QueryParametersRoute<A> extends Route<A>

A query parameters route.

This is used to define route based on the query parameters specified in an input. For instance, in order to resolve a handler for an HTTP request with customer=abc query parameter, a query parameters route must be defined with a parameter matcher for customer parameter targeting the abc customer handler.

Since:
1.12
Author:
Jeremy Kuhn
